topic: Sport Workflow Series (Basketball and NBA finals explorative search")

goals.1: Identify the BGP for basketball player.
goals.3: Identify the BGP for basketball team.
goals.4: Return all italian basketball teams born before 1945 (the result set must be a list of triples basketball team IRI, label and year of inception).
goals.5: Identify the BGP for NBA finals
goals.6: Consider only the basketball teams which Kevin Durant and Lebron James played. Return the number of NBA finals won by these teams (the result set must be a list of triples basketball team IRI, label and #victories. Return a number for each basketball team).
goals.7: Consider only NBA (National Basketball Association) basketball teams and all basketball players who played in one of these teams at least once. Also consider the country of citizenship of the players with the related continent. Return for each continent the number of players who played in an NBA basketball teams. (the result set must be triples of continent IRI, labels and #players)
goals.8: Identify the BGP for the NBA Most Valuable Player Award (MVP) (see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award)
goals.9: Consider the players who won the NBA Most Valuable Player Award. Return for these players the number of NBA Most Valuable Player Award won in their career (the result set must be triples of player IRI, label and #victories)

name: 01f70b5780

1.narrative:
query example
Let's explore the properties of Lebron James to find what makes him a baskketball player
1.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?name ?obj ?objname WHERE { wd:Q36159 ?p ?obj . ?p sc:name ?name. ?obj sc:name ?objname. } LIMIT 20
output: Laureus World Sports Award for Breakthrough of the Year
on focus list of Wikimedia project
Laureus World Sports Award for Sportsman of the Year
execution_output: on focus list of Wikimedia project
Laureus World Sports Award for Sportsman of the Year
Sports Illustrated Sportsperson of the Year

1.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?basketballPlayer ?name WHERE { ?basketballPlayer wdt:P106 wd:Q3665646 ; wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?basketballPlayer sc:name ?name } LIMIT 20

2.narrative:
write your queries
Query to find entities that are subclasses of entities with "basketball in their name"
2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?basketball ?name WHERE { ?basketball wdt:P279 wd:Q877517 . ?basketball sc:name ?name. FILTER regex(?name, ".*basketball.*", "i") } LIMIT 20
SELECT DISTINCT ?basketball ?name WHERE { ?basketball wdt:P279 wd:Q877517 . ?basketball sc:name ?name. FILTER regex(?name, ".*basketball.*", "i") } LIMIT 20

3.narrative:
write your queries
Looking back at our query to explor a basketball player's properties
3.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?team ?name WHERE { ?team wdt:P31 wd:Q13393265 . ?team sc:name ?name . } LIMIT 20
SELECT DISTINCT ?team ?name WHERE { ?team wdt:P31 wd:Q13393265 . ?team sc:name ?name . } LIMIT 20

4.narrative:
write your queries
Let's look at all the properties of a team
4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?team WHERE { ?team wdt:P31 wd:Q13393265 ; wdt:P17 wd:Q38 ; wdt:P571 ?inceptionYear ; ?p ?obj . ?p sc:name ?pName . FILTER (YEAR(?inceptionYear) < 1945) } LIMIT 20

SELECT DISTINCT ?team ?name YEAR(?inceptionYear) as ?yearOfInception WHERE { ?team wdt:P31 wd:Q13393265 ; wdt:P17 wd:Q38 ; wdt:P571 ?inceptionYear . ?team sc:name ?name . FILTER (YEAR(?inceptionYear) < 1945) } LIMIT 20

5.narrative:
write your queries
This query is to find some NBA finals entities to explore
Its output is the IRI and lable of the subject, predicate, and object respectivly, filtered for objects that have "NBA finals" in their lable
5.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?final ?name WHERE { ?final wdt:P31 wd:Q842375 . ?final sc:name ?name . FILTER regex(?name, ".*NBA final.*", "i") } LIMIT 20
SELECT DISTINCT ?final ?name WHERE { ?final wdt:P31 wd:Q842375 . ?final sc:name ?name . FILTER regex(?name, ".*NBA final.*", "i") } LIMIT 20

6.narrative:
write your queries
Let's explore the properties of Lebron James to find what links him a baskketball team
The property "member of sports team" IRI P54 seems like what we're looking for. Let's explre it further
6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?team ?name count(?s) as ?victories WHERE { {wd:Q36159 wdt:P54 ?team} UNION {wd:Q29545 wdt:P54 ?team} . OPTIONAL {?s wdt:P1346 ?team. ?s sc:name ?sName. FILTER regex(?sName, "[0-9] NBA Finals")} . ?team sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?team ?name LIMIT 100
output: United States men's national basketball team
execution_output: United States men's national basketball team

6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?team ?name count(?s) as ?victories WHERE { {wd:Q36159 wdt:P54 ?team} UNION {wd:Q29545 wdt:P54 ?team} . OPTIONAL {?s wdt:P1346 ?team. ?s sc:name ?sName. FILTER regex(?sName, "[0-9] NBA Finals")} . ?team sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?team ?name LIMIT 100
output: United States men's national basketball team
execution_output: United States men's national basketball team

7.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?continent ?continentName count(?basketballPlayer) as ?players WHERE { ?basketballPlayer wdt:P106 wd:Q3665646 ; wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?basketballPlayer wdt:P27 ?country. ?country wdt:P30 ?continent . ?basketballPlayer sc:name ?name . ?continent sc:name ?continentName. } GROUP BY ?continent ?continentName LIMIT 20

SELECT DISTINCT ?continent ?continentName count(?basketballPlayer) as ?players WHERE { ?basketballPlayer wdt:P106 wd:Q3665646 ; wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?basketballPlayer wdt:P27 ?country. ?country wdt:P30 ?continent . ?basketballPlayer sc:name ?name . ?continent sc:name ?continentName. } GROUP BY ?continent ?continentName LIMIT 20

8.narrative:
write your queries
Let's explore the properties of Lebron James to find if he's ever won the award
We have a "award received" IRI P166. We can explore it
8.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?award ?name WHERE { ?award wdt:P31 wd:Q652965 . ?award sc:name ?name. FILTER regex(?name, "^NBA Most Valuable Player Award", "i") } LIMIT 20
SELECT DISTINCT ?award ?name WHERE { ?award wdt:P31 wd:Q652965 . ?award sc:name ?name. FILTER regex(?name, "^NBA Most Valuable Player Award", "i") } LIMIT 20

9.narrative:
write your queries
Let's find all the instances of a player winnig the award
9.query: SELECT ?basketballPlayer ?name count(?award) as ?victories WHERE { ?basketballPlayer wdt:P106 wd:Q3665646 ; wdt:P31 wd:Q5 ; wdt:P166 ?award . ?award wdt:P31 wd:Q652965 . ?basketballPlayer sc:name ?name . ?award sc:name ?awardName . FILTER regex(?awardName, "^NBA Most Valuable Player Award", "i") } GROUP BY ?basketballPlayer ?name ORDER BY ?name LIMIT 30

SELECT ?basketballPlayer ?name count(?award) as ?victories WHERE { ?basketballPlayer wdt:P106 wd:Q3665646 ; wdt:P31 wd:Q5 ; wdt:P166 ?award . ?award wdt:P31 wd:Q652965 . ?basketballPlayer sc:name ?name . ?award sc:name ?awardName . FILTER regex(?awardName, "^NBA Most Valuable Player Award", "i") } GROUP BY ?basketballPlayer ?name ORDER BY ?name LIMIT 30
